---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Insulation Pakenham | Heritage Homes & Estate New Builds | (03) 9003 0108"
  description="Insulation for Pakenham — heritage pre-2000 ceiling retrofits (high VEU eligibility), underfloor batts on weatherboard, cavity pump-fill on 1980s brick, Pakenham Springs estate work. Free assessment."
  canonical="https://beaconsfieldinsulation.com.au/pakenham/">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Pakenham &middot; biggest retrofit opportunity in the shire</span>
      <h1>Insulation in <span class="accent">Pakenham</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Pakenham has the largest insulation-retrofit opportunity in Cardinia
        Shire &mdash; established town with a lot of pre-2000 housing stock,
        empty wall cavities and ceiling insulation under R2.0, plus the
        newer Pakenham Springs and Lakeside estates for first-fit and
        top-up work. High VIC Energy Upgrades (VEU) rebate eligibility.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book a free assessment</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Why Pakenham</span>
      <h2>The Pakenham insulation story.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>Pre-2000 housing &mdash; high VEU eligibility.</h3>
        <p>
          Old Pakenham (around the CBD, John Street, Henry Street, Princes
          Hwy north) is mostly 1970s&ndash;1990s brick veneer and weatherboard
          on standard quarter-acre blocks. Original ceiling insulation is
          typically R2.0 or lower (sometimes none); wall cavities are
          empty; floors are usually concrete slab but some weatherboard
          cottages have suspended timber. The combination &mdash; minimum
          R-value, empty cavities, on a gas-bill-burning open-plan layout
          &mdash; makes Pakenham the highest-impact retrofit suburb in
          Cardinia Shire.
        </p>
        <p>
          VIC Energy Upgrades (VEU) rebate eligibility runs around
          50&ndash;60% of pre-2000 Pakenham owner-occupied and rental homes.
          For those properties the rebate covers 50&ndash;70% of the ceiling
          upgrade cost &mdash; typical out-of-pocket $1,500&ndash;$3,500
          for a 180m&sup2; ceiling retrofit.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Pakenham Springs / Lakeside / new estates.</h3>
        <p>
          The newer estates south of the freeway (Pakenham Springs,
          Lakeside) are 2010+ builds with R3.5&ndash;R5.0 ceiling already
          and R2.5 walls. The conversation is usually NatHERS 7-star
          compliance on first fit, ceiling R-value top-up to R6.0/R7.0, or
          adding acoustic batts to the media room. VEU eligibility is
          lower here because original R-values usually exceed the R2.0
          threshold.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Heritage Pakenham &mdash; honest conversations.</h3>
        <p>
          Pre-1950 heritage Pakenham homes are solid-brick without a cavity
          to fill. We'll honestly walk through the options at site visit:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>External EIFS render system (expensive, changes appearance, needs heritage approval)</li>
          <li>Internal stud-wall lining (loses 75mm floor space per wall, plaster work)</li>
          <li>Accept walls stay R0.4, invest in ceiling + underfloor + draft-sealing instead (usually the best $-per-comfort outcome on heritage homes)</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Typical Pakenham jobs.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Pre-2000 brick veneer ceiling retrofit ($4.5K&ndash;$7K, often net $1.5K&ndash;$3K after VEU)</li>
          <li>External cavity pump-fill on 1985 brick veneer ($4.5K&ndash;$7K)</li>
          <li>Underfloor polyester batts on weatherboard cottage ($3.5K&ndash;$6K)</li>
          <li>Heritage home ceiling + underfloor + draft-sealing combination ($7K&ndash;$11K)</li>
          <li>Pakenham Springs estate NatHERS 7-star first-fit ($4K&ndash;$8K)</li>
          <li>Townhouse NCC F5 party-wall acoustic ($180&ndash;$280/m&sup2;)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Other service areas.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/beaconsfield/">Beaconsfield</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/officer/">Officer</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/cardinia-lakes/">Cardinia Lakes</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/heritage-springs/">Heritage Springs</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/cardinia-shire/">All Cardinia Shire</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free Pakenham insulation assessment.</h2>
        <p>Highest VEU eligibility in the shire. Heritage-honest advice. Fixed quote in 48 hours.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
